<!DOCTYPE task PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Task//EN" "task.dtd">
<task id="task_m5t_sf1_pvb">
    <title>Deployment Using <ph conkeyref="PRODvars/PRODUCT_SERVER_ALTERNATIVE_NAME"/></title>
    <taskbody>
        <context>
            <p>Agents installed in <b>Managed</b> mode are managed by a <ph
                    conkeyref="PRODvars/PRODUCT_SERVER_ALTERNATIVE_NAME"/> server, which can issue
                remote commands to all managed agents. To deploy agent configuration settings to
                multiple managed agents, launch the <ph
                    conkeyref="PRODvars/PRODUCT_SERVER_ALTERNATIVE_NAME"/> web console and use the
                    <uicontrol>Send Command </uicontrol>menu located on the
                    <wintitle>Agent</wintitle> management screen.</p>
            <sectiondiv>
                <data>
                    <title><b>Remotely Exporting Agent Settings</b></title>
                </data>
                <p>You can remotely obtain agent configuration settings and Approved Lists by
                    exporting and downloading them from the <ph
                        conkeyref="PRODvars/PRODUCT_SERVER_ALTERNATIVE_NAME"/>.</p>
            </sectiondiv>
        </context>
        <steps>
            <step>
                <cmd>Click <menucascade>
                        <uicontrol>Agents</uicontrol>
                        <uicontrol><text otherprops="SPLM">StellarProtect (Legacy Mode)</text><text
                                otherprops="SE">StellarEnforce</text></uicontrol>
                    </menucascade> from the <ph conkeyref="PRODvars/PRODUCT_SERVER_ALTERNATIVE_NAME"
                    /> web console. The <wintitle>Agent</wintitle> management screen appears.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Select the target endpoint(s).</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Click <uicontrol>Import/ Export</uicontrol> and select one of the
                    following:</cmd>
                <info>
                    <ul id="ul_uv1_nds_yvb">
                        <li>
                            <p><uicontrol>Import Approved List</uicontrol></p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p><uicontrol>Import Agent Configuration</uicontrol></p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>The <ph conkeyref="PRODvars/PRODUCT_SERVER_ALTERNATIVE_NAME"/> will issue the
                        command. Progress can be viewed from the pop-up
                                <b><wintitle>Details</wintitle></b> window.</p>
                </info>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>To export settings, repeat the above steps, instead selecting either
                        <uicontrol>Export Approved List</uicontrol> or<uicontrol> Export Agent
                        Configuration</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>A <wintitle>Command Deployment</wintitle> window appears showing the exports
                    status.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Click <uicontrol>Download</uicontrol> to download the exported settings.</cmd>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
</task>
